Cross River State Police Command has said it recorded a crime-free Easter. Commissioner of Police (CP) Kayode Akande, speaking on Tuesday during the parade of 34 suspects, said: “We are re-engineering our security tactics and so far they are yielding good results. We have done a test run of the digitalisation of the security coverage.” He said three locally-made pistols, charms, iron windows, one live cartridge, one short axe, N368,000, one Passat Wago car with registration number AKU 365 HT, electric poles, two knives and one phone were recovered.